The paper proposes optimization algorithms for Poisson likelihood modeling, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper discusses the use of these algorithms in imaging, social networks, and time series analysis, which are all areas that fall under the umbrella of machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
